definition.value: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and 4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl.
The (13S)-stereoisomer of HOTrE.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid substituted with a methoxy group at C-3 and a polyprenyl chain of unspecified length at C-5.
The hydroxybenzoate anion formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid. The major species present at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of thromboxanes B that is (5Z,13E,17Z)-thromboxa-5,13,17-trien-1-oic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 9, 11 and 15.
Any ceramide where the sphingoid component is specified as heptadecasphingosine.
A dihydroxybenzoic acid where the hydroxy groups are at the 4- and 5-positions together with a heptaprenyl group at the 3-position.
The (5Z,8Z,10E,14Z)-stereoisomer of 12-HETE.
A methyl ketone that is acetone in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a 1-methylpyrrolidin-2-yl group.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of hygrine and (--hygrine.
A 3,4-dihydroxy-5-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 7 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
A dihydroxybenzoic acid where the hydroxy groups are at the 4- and 5-positions together with a octaprenyl group at the 3-position.
A 3,4-dihydroxy-5-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 8 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid in which the polyprenyl component is specified as heptaprenyl.
A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl component is specified as heptaprenyl.
A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoic acid in which the polyprenyl component is specified as octaprenyl.
A 3-methoxy-4-hydroxy-5-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl component is specified as octaprenyl.
A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 5-hydroxystearic acid.
A  triacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1, 2 and 3 are specified as oleoyl, linoleoyl and linoleoyl respectively.
A monocarboxylic acid amide that is tetradecanamide substituted by an oxo group at position 3 and a (3S)-2-oxotetrahydrofuran-3-yl group at the N atom.
A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 10-hydroxystearic acid.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-heptadecanoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine; major species at pH 7.3.
An RNA fragment comprised of three cytidine, three guanosine and two uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-G-U-U-C-G-C-G.
A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 11-hydroxystearic acid.
A lysophosphatidylcholine with defined stereochemistry where the position of the acyl group is unknown.
A phosphatidylserine 36:2(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-stearoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine; major species at pH 7.3.
A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 12-hydroxystearic acid.
A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 13-hydroxystearic acid.
A phosphatidylcholine 37:4 in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylglycerol(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-palmitoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
An alkylglycerol that is any 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol bearing an additional methyl substituent at position 2.
A glycerol ether that is any 1-alkyl-3-acyl-sn-glycerol bearing an additional methyl substituent at position 2.
A 1-acylglycero-3-phospho-1'-glycerol(1-) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as hexadecanoyl; major species at pH 7.3.
A N-hexacosenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine consisting of sphingosine as the sphingoid base acylated at the N atom by a (17Z)-hexacosenoyl group.
A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 7-hydroxystearic acid.
A tertiary alcohol that consists of propan-1-ol substituted by a cyclohexyl and a phenyl group at position 1 and a pyrrolidin-1-yl group at position 3.

An RNA fragment comprised of six cytidine, seven guanosine, seven adenosine and five uridine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence C-G-A-A-A-G-U-C-C-G-A-U-C-G-G-C-G-U-A-A-U-G-U-C-A.
Any carboxamide obtained by acylation of both the amino and hydroxy functions of ethanolamine.

An RNA fragment comprised of seven guanosine, five uridine, eight cytidine and four adenosine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence G-U-U-U-G-G-C-G-A-C-G-U-C-C-C-A-C-A-U-G-A-G-C-C.
Any 1-O-acyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the N-acyl group is specified as acetyl.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the acyl group specified is heneicosanoyl.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in whihc the acyl group specified is nonadecanoyl.
A FAHFA obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of palmitic acid with the hydroxy group of 8-hydroxystearic acid.
A N-octadecenolsphingosine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is 9Z-octadecenoyl.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the acyl group specified is heptadecanoyl.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
